    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Milewski uses Haskell tuples and <code>Either</code>, plus C++ <code>std::pair</code> and tagged unions. Here, Scheme lists stand in for pairs and tagged lists for Either. Factorizers are direct translations of his Haskell definitions. The "ranking candidates" section makes the universal construction concrete: a triple is a worse product candidate than a pair because the triple factors through the pair. Milewski also covers the product/coproduct asymmetry in Set: functions are total (defined everywhere) but not necessarily surjective (covering the codomain).</p>

